242	vovimayhem	Transition Guards actually making changes to inventory	I've seen this a couple of times on the state machines:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n\r\nevent :finish do\r\n    transition ready: :out_for_delivery, if: ->(order) { order.output }\r\nend\r\n\r\n```\r\nThat `if` is actually changing the inventory right now... but what happens if before that, I just wish to use the `can_finish?` method, so I can know if the order is ready to finish? Exactly, it actually runs the output, changing the inventory when I just wanted to check if it's ready!!\r\n\r\nI'm changing `OutflowOrder` state machine so it only runs the validation, while moving the inventory output to a before_transition callback:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n# StateTransitions::ForOutflowOrders\r\n        event :finish do\r\n          transition ready: :out_for_delivery, if: ->(order) { order.valid_inventory_output? }\r\n        end\r\n\r\n        before_transition to: :out_for_delivery do |order|\r\n          order.output_inventory!\r\n        end\r\n\r\n        after_transition to: :out_for_delivery do |order|\r\n          order.shelves.each(&:update_status)\r\n\r\n          # Close the order unless there's a truck with no driver or company:\r\n          order.close_order if order.all_truck_loads_have_driver_name_and_company?\r\n        end\r\n\r\n# OutflowOrder\r\n  def output_inventory!\r\n    return unless valid_inventory_output?\r\n    Rts::InventoryOutputter.new(self).output\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def valid_inventory_output?\r\n    validator = InventoryOutputValidator.new self\r\n    validator.validate!\r\n    validator.errors.each { |error| key, msg = error; errors[:base] << msg }\r\n  end\r\n```\r\n\r\n*WE NEED TO FIND* other places where this is being done - I remember `InflowOrder` also has this behaviour, and although no current code makes use of the `can_*?` method, when we optimise problems will start.	\N	closed	34	2016-08-05 20:49:51.682603	2016-08-05 20:49:51.682603	184	142087199	\N	2016-03-19 18:03:14 UTC
