460	danlozano	Call main queue in ApiClient class	Instead of having your API calls like this:\r\n\r\n```swift\r\nApiClient.sharedApiClient.fetchOrganization("icalialabs") { (organization) in\r\n            self.getCompanyImage(organization, imageView: self.companyImage)\r\n            TechViewController.controller.organization = organization\r\n            dispatch_async(dispatch_get_main_queue()) {\r\n                self.companyDesctiptionLabel.text = organization.desctiption\r\n                self.companyNameLabel.text = organization.name\r\n                self.tableView.reloadData()\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhere you always have to call the main queue to update UI.\r\n\r\nYou can call the completion block, on the main queue, from the API Client's methods, that way all view controllers that use any of API Client's methods are automatically on the main queue.\r\n\r\n```swift\r\nlet task = NSURLSession.sharedSession().dataTaskWithURL(URL!) { (data, response, error) in\r\n            do {\r\n                let dictionary = try NSJSONSerialization.JSONObjectWithData(data!, options: []) as! NSDictionary\r\n                let arrayOfDictionaries = dictionary["issues"] as! NSArray\r\n                \r\n                for dictionary in arrayOfDictionaries {\r\n                    let issue = Issue()\r\n                    issue.initialize(dictionary as! NSDictionary)\r\n                    arrayOfIssues.append(issue)\r\n                }\r\n              \r\n            }\r\n            catch{\r\n                print("Error")\r\n            }\r\n            dispatch_async(dispatch_get_main_queue(), {\r\n                completion(arrayOfIssues)\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        task.resume()\r\n```	\N	open	60	2016-08-08 14:37:02.056822	2016-08-08 14:37:02.056822	26	168738500	\N	2016-08-01 20:48:07 UTC
461	danlozano	Avoid IUO's!	#### Avoid Implicitly Unwrapped Optionals\r\n\r\nIUO's are basically optionals, BUT they are automatically unwrapped when used, making then un-safe. There are some (small) cases when you should/need to use them, but not very frequently.\r\n\r\n```swift\r\nvar commits: [Commit]!\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn this case in **TechViewController**, instead of having that you could have:\r\n\r\n```swift\r\nvar commits: [Commit]?\r\n```\r\n\r\nand whenever you want to use it you have to unwrap it\r\n\r\n```swift\r\nif let commits = commits {\r\n   doSomething(commits[1])\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nor, you can avoid the optional in this case by having an initial empty value.\r\n\r\n```swift\r\nvar commits: [Commit] = []\r\n```\r\n\r\nRefactor all View Controllers / classes that use IUO's.	\N	closed	60	2016-08-08 14:37:02.067515	2016-08-08 14:37:02.067515	25	168737922	\N	2016-08-01 20:45:10 UTC
